help i need to get organised time saving tricks needed please my work day ends and my housework begins i am in need of some time saving tricks that work for you please and thanks i love to use my crock pot and freeze ahead meals if i know i'm making lasagna i'll make and freeze one that saves a lot of time and energy down the line i also love kraftfoodandfamily magazine you can sign up for it on their website lots of recipies and shopping lists and coupons i start a load of laundry at night and put it in the dryer before i leave to keep up with the daily stuff i also have my husband help me in the evening pick up all the kids toys and i vacuum or i clean the kitchen at night so it's ready to go in the morning do what works for you i also like to pour bleach down my drains once a month toilet sink and i fill the bathtub with really hot water and the next morning i empty and wipe out the tub and swish flush the toilet and wipe the sink i love antibacterial wipes i give the surfaces a good wipe down i also use basket to store kids toys and things that don't belong in a particular room i them go around and place the items in the room they go in or if company is coming stash it in a closet until i can get to it good luck Toilet Autonomous building Customs and etiquette of Japan Japanese toilet Dishwashing Textile manufacturing The Inside Casting Menstrual cup Futurama (TV series - season 4) Cruising (maritime) Japanese tea ceremony Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Water Flush toilet Sento Toilet paper Urinal Coffee Shaggy dog story Bidet Washing machine Brewery USS Tang (SS-306) Toilet humour Bathroom Slow cooker Thermal power station Sears Holdings Corporation Neopets Au pair USS Tunny (SS-282) USS Trigger (SS-237) Dry cleaning Operation Petticoat Solar power Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Chinglish Genericized trademark Siphon Aerial (dance move) Daylight saving time Dishwasher Dialysis Sewage treatment Water (molecule) Greywater USS Whale (SS-239) 